<br>
- Weeks farming tradeskill supplies, so you can get 1 point of gain in your skill.<br>
<br>
- Random rare spawns that get ganked by any level 30 for their own use instead of the use it was intended for.<br>
<br>
- Rare spawns, with uber rare drops<br>
<br>
- Spells that prove to be as useless as tissue paper in a swimming pool.<br>
<br>
- Hidden limits on pets and spells that go beyond that limit, decieving us into incorrect thinking.<br>
<br>
...and the list goes on.<br>
<br>
It should be about fun. It should most definately be about having a good time, but sadly, it's turned into a massive time sink alone. Time sink = more money spent to play = more money/longetivity to Verant.<br>
<br>
